<main>
I have to remind myself sometimes that it’s healthy to be among the living.

We talked a lot about you coming to visit but it was never a good time with work and with your exams.

Now, whenever I walk around the city I think of you and the places we could have gone together.

The way I imagine it, you’re the life and soul, of course. And I’m the awkward older sister. You bum cigarettes from me all night. You keep saying that you’ll get a pack when you can get change for the machine but that never happens and I know it won’t but I don’t care.

You crack jokes that are really not in any way acceptable because you know I’ll try not to laugh at them and fail and you’ve always loved that.

There’s not a single place here I haven’t imagined you being. So many strangers I’ve seen from behind and almost called out your name before stopping myself.

How can there not be more time?

