I’ve looked for signs of you in so many places. I can’t even tell you how many false idols I’ve worshipped.

I have no convictions. If Satan himself told me he could give me a sign from you, I’d be scratching a pentagram on my kitchen floor in no time, sacrificing a goat.

I’ve tried mediums. Tarot cards. Hypnosis. Tea-leaves. Coffee grinds. Electrical currents.

You name it.

But it’s a one way conversation.

I know this is morbid but, looking at her, it was the closest I’ve
come in three years. And now they’ve taken her away too. They’ll find out more about her, I’m sure. Put her on display in a museum. So she’ll stop being mine as well.

