<<set $passage to "RP-23">><<set $nextpassage to "RP-24">><<audio ":all" stop>><<audio "RP_23" play>>
<main>
This city has changed. It looks so different and I don’t know why. Here I stand on the road to Verulamium. Her family wouldn’t tell me where her resting place was. I searched for it among the burial grounds to the North East of the City. I asked strangers. A morbid request. The more polite said they didn’t know.

Most stared at me as if I were diseased and moved away.

I only wanted to mourn her.

I wish I could see her face. When I close my eyes, I can picture a girl. When I left she was only thirteen. How had it changed? Does it matter now?

I wish I could have known her better.

To understand what it was about her that I loved.

Oh all-powerful Mithras, is there nothing you can say to comfort me? After all the pain I suffered for you. Give me something.

I try not to think of those last moments. Instead I imagine you an hour before at the party, smoking, making people laugh. Doing impressions of whoever. The good part of me wants you to be at rest but there’s another part of me that -

I mean sure you know I can be selfish. You’d say it yourself. And the selfish part of me doesn’t want you at rest. Ripped away like that in a car crash. The unjustness of it. That it might keep you here.

I’d rather be haunted, tormented by you than have you disappear. It’s the absence I can’t stand. The absolute brutality of it.

Barbaric.

Don’t be gone. Let me know you’re there. Please. Please. Let me know you’re there. Give me something.

